gobblin.async

Class AsyncDataDispatcher<D>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.google.common.util.concurrent.AbstractExecutionThreadService
      • gobblin.async.AsyncDataDispatcher<D>
  • Type Parameters:
    D - type of record
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Service
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    AbstractAsyncDataWriter

    @NotThreadSafe
public abstract class AsyncDataDispatcher<D>
extends AbstractExecutionThreadService
    Base class with skeleton logic to dispatch a record asynchronously. It buffers the records and consumes them by run()

    However the records are consumed depends on the actual implementation of dispatch(Queue), which may process one record or a batch at a time

        protected abstract void dispatch(Queue<D> buffer)
                          throws DispatchException
        Synchronously dispatch records in the buffer. Retries should be done if necessary. Every record consumed from the buffer must have its callback called if any.
        Parameters:
        buffer - the buffer which contains a collection of records
        Throws:
        DispatchException - if dispatch failed
